item.description:
Put this little vim script in your .vimrc to rerun the previous command with the bang (!) by just typing :Please.
function! BangLastCommand() &quot; The last command that was run is stored in the register `:` (:registers) let lastcommand = split(@:, ' ') let command = lastcommand[0] . '! ' . join(lastcommand[1:], ' ') execute command endfunction command! Please call BangLastCommand()  So, now, if you do:
:e ~/.vimrc  And you get an error because the current file has to be save, something like:
